she nudges me out of my comfort zone & helps me back to it when i overdo it. she always validates my sexuality & makes sure that i’m included

she rewatches my comfort movies with me. over & over & over again. she never complains when we get in the car & listen to the same 5 songs for 2 weeks straight. she lets me rant about how amazing the movies & songs are.
she is goofy with me & makes me laugh. she teases me. she has inside jokes with me & always slips them in when i’m feeling overwhelmed with other people. it’s like a little signal.

she understands that i loved my dad more than anything but that he & i had a complicated relationship & that im still angry with him sometimes. she listens to me wrestle with wanting him back but also knowing that if he were here, we probably wouldn’t be in speaking terms.

the one that chokes me up to even think about: she never questions my grief. she is present & gentle & reassuring. she lets me talk about my dad, even if it’s the same stories she’s heard before (& someday they will be,, because there won’t be any new stories)
she is willing to work through disagreements with me, even when it’s inconvenient. even when we don’t agree,, we both walk away with more understanding & compassion.
she set up my desk in the office & moved it multiple times for me. she helped me decorate & listened while i told her all about interior design
she says “knock knock” before coming into a room so i don’t get scared

she remembers my triggers and provides comfort when they happen in public and finds “work arounds” for at home. when she’s using a knife in the kitchen, or turning on the disposal, she’s gives me a heads up.

she encourages me to eat, but doesn’t make anything conditional & never gets angry if i don’t. she celebrated my wins,, no matter how small. the first time i went grocery shopping without having a meltdown or crying,, she made a point to say “babe look at you! that was amazing!”
she buys food she knows i like & sometimes new things that i “might be able to eat, but no pressure”. she also pays attention to my hyper fixation food & makes sure we have it on hand.

she is patient and understanding of my sensory issues. she also looks for ways to include more stimulation in things, such as lights that correspond with our tv - bc she thought it would be fun for me.

she hypes up my new outfits,, especially when she knows i have a big work meeting. she also listens to me work through the list of “rules” for outfits. 

& gives her honest opinions and kindly counteracts my ridiculous* reasons for vetoing 

*ridiculous being my ocd

she kisses my forehead as shes falling asleep, holds my hand or wraps her arm around me. 

when i have nightmares she whispers “you’re safe. i’m here. no one can get to you. it’s okay honey, im right here”

she tells me i’m beautiful like 15 times a day. & always in an “awed” tone of voice like she’s seeing me for the first time. 

*sigh* “wow,, you’re beeeeaaaauuutiifuuul” 😍

it is late & i am tired & i am sad & my gf is asleep next to me & she is wonderful & beautiful & so kind & gentle & dare i say also very funny & so here’s a thread about all* the little things she does for me that make my heart explode.
